properties.opinion: Beim zweiten Besuch total enttäuscht worden, nie wieder Badhüsli! Das Essen ist zwar mega lecker, der Ort ein Traum, aber: unwillig wurde uns ein Platz zugewiesen, uns wurde die Deko auf dem Tisch unter den Händen weggezogen (obwohl keine Gewitter drohte und nicht Dienstschluss war), keine Nachfrage nach Nachtisch oder Kaffee, kein Danke beim Bezahlen, kein Abschliedsgruss. Also so etwas Unfreundliches wie die ältere Bedienung (Besitzerin?) haben wir noch nie erlebt. Dabei sind wir extra mit dem Rad von Kreuzlingen angeradelt und hatten telefonisch reserviert, was auch sehr unfreundlich angenommen wurde. Nie wieder Badhüsli!

properties.name: Gasthof Ochsen
properties.opinion: Ideale Übernachtungsmöglichkeit auf dem Alpenpanorama-Weg (Etappe Schwägalp - Stein). Preiswerter Landgasthof mit rustikalem Charme und renovierten Badezimmern. Sehr empfehlenswert.

properties.name: The Monkey Puzzle
properties.opinion:
Cosy and friendly vibe. Nice food. You can almost always get a table at this pub. Feels like a sneaky little gem because it's a little hidden away, not near a tube station, in quite a residential area. It never gets over-crowded even at peak after-work hours
Our favourite OSMLondon meet-up venue!

properties.name: Bergrestaurant Gamplüt
properties.opinion:
Ich war mit 2 Hunden an der Bahn und 3 Pers. und ein Hund warteten schon da. Es gesellten sich dann noch 2 Pers. dazu und wir warteten und warteten. Nach 20 min. läutete die eine Person um nachzufragen ob und wann die Bahn fährt. Eine schnauzige Frauenstimme sagte: In etwa 10 min fahren wir. Das ist ja der Hammer! in einer halben Stunde laufe ich normal nach oben, aber sowas ohne Entschuldigung oder Grund die Gäste in der Talstation schmoren lassen! Unzumutbar!!
2 Personen entfernten sich bevor sie in die Gondel stiegen. Jetzt kommen die Touristen einfach ohne ihr Dazutun. Irgendwann ändert das, hoffe für euch auch! Ich komme jedenfalls NIE mehr wie viele andere auch!

properties.name: Camping Cavresc'
properties.opinion: Nice little camping near the Lago di Poschiavo. Facilities are in good condition.

properties.name: BAMBULE Kletterhalle
properties.opinion:
es gibt lange Routen (16 Meter Höhe) und  einen Bereich kurze Routen (8-10m?) und einen kleinen Boulderbereich. Es gibt auch 2  Toppas Automaten (nicht verschiebar).
Alles ganz neu und für mich als Kletter-Anfänger (6a max.)   ganz schön

properties.opinion: Large dog park with lots of paths, different vegetation, benches and a picnic table. At the south entrance at the parking lot there is a waste bin and free dog waste bags.

properties.name: Zeltlagerplatz Naturns
properties.opinion: Bestehend aus mehreren kleinen Terrassen mit viel natürlicher Beschattung durch Bäume. Das Waschhaus besteht aus zwei Wassertoiletten, zwei Duschen (1 warm) und 6 Waschbecken. Trinkwasser steht unbegrenzt zur Verfügung. Die Feuerstelle ist mit 3 Bankreihen ringsrum schön angelegt. Etwas Strom steht über eine Photovoltaikablage und eine Pufferbatterie bereit.

properties.name: Camping Latsch
properties.opinion: Netter Campingplatz direkt an der Etsch gelegen. Hat ein Außenpool mit Rutsche sowie einem kleinen beheizten Indoorbecken. Die Sanitäranlagen sind ausreichend dimensioniert und gepflegt. Abzug gibt der Verkehrslärm der Bundesstraße, v.a. tagsüber.

properties.name: Meiersalp
properties.opinion: Wie immer speditiv und freundlich, mit angemessenem Preis/Leistungsverhältnis!

properties.name: Lakeview Campground
properties.opinion: May 22-24, 2022 - Toilets maintained daily, a grill and picnic table at every campsite, and the amazing location make this an awesome campground.

properties.name: Frankie & Benny's

properties.name: Nordstern
properties.opinion: Open sky, view of stars exceptionally clear. Vehicles from federal road at 800 m audible. Café Chalet at 4 km.

properties.name: Area Attrezzata Camper
properties.opinion: Drinkable water point and water pipe (approx 2m), waste water disposal. Quiet, in working days some low noise around 8 due to cars parking in nearby plant. No amenities around. If you are not in need of water services, there are better places around.

properties.name: Resonate Coffee
properties.opinion: Coffee isn't bad. Small- ishcafé, with a bike rack for customers.

properties.name: Seafront Boulder
properties.opinion: Cool climbing boulder gym!

properties.name: Veli Jože
properties.opinion:
Location is nice, almost all parcels have shadow and it is a good place for snorkeling. Two little cobblestone beaches, sea inflatable games (fee), boat slide, and fast food, convenience store and a little greengrocer. Camp is affiliated with schools, so there could be music and games, not later than 11PM.  If you need extra tranquillity, you can camp outside parcels, 100m away from the sea under the pines. Wide meadow for playing.
Eating outside alert: fast food use to shut down at 9:30PM and other restaurants in the area seem to have the same schedule, even in high season.
Camp prices are a little below the average; boat rental (pedal boat 25 euros an hour) and water games rather expensive (bring your own SUP).

properties.name: Vallevecchia
properties.opinion: Grass and ground surface parking with almost no shadow. Showers with token. Toilets are free (as far as I remember). The whole area is subject to mosquitos after sunset. The site features one of the few remaining natural beaches of northern Adriatic, known as "La Brussa". Beach is sandy and cleaned at the beginning of summer. Shadowed paths in the wood.

properties.name: Camping Ulika
properties.opinion: Superclean and well organized. Many activities for children and daily aquagymn (pool relatively cold). Ping-pong tables (bring your net), minigolf. Three good restaurants ("Grill" has particularly bargain menues for dinner). Small lovely cobblestone beach close to the pool. Here crystal sea water, while north and south shores are less clear. Prices soar in high season. Coast footway/bikeway to Porec with some parts shared with cars.

properties.name: Autocamp Korada
properties.opinion: Basic, small camp. Nice location on swimmable river. Walking distance from center. Features a relatively cheap restaurant with quality regional dishes and even pizza.

properties.name: Kanal
properties.opinion: Basic, small camp. Nice location on swimmable river. Walking distance from center. Cheap restaurant with quality regional dishes and even pizza.

properties.name: Kamp Karlo
properties.opinion:
Host rather selective: camp was about half occupation, but she didn't accept us, declaring 
- she was waiting for other people 
- max allowable capacity reached
- camp does not accept reservation.
It sounded unconsistent and rather an excuse, so we left.

properties.name: Sidro
properties.opinion: Basic, informal camp. Could be a backup accomodation in high season for small tents when other are completely booked/full.

properties.name: Camping Marelago
properties.opinion: Sehr schöner Campingplatz, wir sind hier schon mehrere Jahre und kommen immer gerne wieder her. Es ist nicht weit zum Meer und alles was man braucht ist hier vorhanden.

properties.name: Charlottenlund Hundeskov
properties.opinion: It is a huge dog park mostly covered by a beach tree forest, so there is plenty of shade on a warm summer day. And you can eat or have a drink at nearby Jorden Rundt or Bomhuset.

properties.name: Camping Au Donau
properties.opinion: Moderner Campingplatz mit großer Zeltwiese und allem was man braucht. Biergarten und Backwaren gibt es auch. Der Platz ist sogar gesichert und kann nur mit einem Zugangscode betreten werden.

properties.name: Camping Kohlbachmühle
properties.opinion: Campingplatz mit schöner Lage - hier kann man sein Zelt direkt an der Donau aufstellen. Das Essen und die Duschen waren auch gut.

properties.name: Camping Donau Strandhaus
properties.opinion: Campingplatz direkt am Rhein, aber leider auch direkt an den Bahnschienen. Duschen waren ok und Steckdosen waren direkt bei den Zeltplätzen vorhanden. Zelten kann man auf einer eher kleinen Grasfläche mit Bäumen.

properties.name: Campingplatz Kelheim-Herrnsaal Poschenrieder
properties.opinion: Nette Camping-Wiese auf einem Bauernhof, direkt am Donau-Radweg. Unkomplizierter Check-In und nettes Personal. Duschen recht sauber.

properties.name: Y Domen-Las
properties.opinion:
When we arrived, the only non-alcoholic drinks were apple juice, cranberry juice and water. Two glasses of apple juice (poured from a supermarket carton) there was only cranberry juice and water.
There was also no ice and we were given a pot containing various condiment sachets including vinegar but not salt, which we had to borrow from the next table over.
The people running the place seemed nice, but clearly not capable of running a restaurant.

properties.name: Red Kite Feeding
properties.opinion: Amazing view from the hide. Must have been almost a hundred birds circling overhead. Went for a walk in the surrounding area and saw many kites still hanging around.

properties.name: Eagles Inn
properties.opinion: Good food and frendly staff.

properties.name: Place Salvador Allende
properties.opinion: Possibilité de stationnement de camping-cars  de nuit moyennant finances ; relocalisation assez récente de grands parkings (place de la Petite Sole et arrière port).

properties.name: Bistro 67
properties.opinion: Das Bistro 67 ist wirklich ein Bijoux der besonderen Klasse. Eine Gastfreundschaft die selten anzutreffen ist. Ein Charme von Weltklasse. Wir haben hier per Zufall (und wir sind sehr froh darüber) ein super Essen mit einer äusserst komfortablen Übernachtung gefunden. Es war seahr spontan, aber der Besitzer hat alles daran gesetzt dass wir uns wohl fühlten. Vielen Dank. Wir werden sicherlich wieder hier einkehren und übernachten. einfach grandios. Familie Kamna

properties.name: Løbegård Kildevældsparken
properties.opinion:
En mindre hundepark med en bænk og en skraldespand.
Der  er træer og buske udenfor hegnet, der giver skygge på en varm dag.
Der er et tykt lag strandsand over det hele, så der bliver aldrig mudret.

properties.name: Juniper Basin
properties.opinion: Apr 1-2, 2022 - Hiking Tanque Verde Peak. Lots of stagnant water, most of it unappealing. The bathroom is all busted up. The area is very pretty. Make sure you go up to the peak from here if you have enough water. Site 3 didn't have a bear box.

properties.name: Grass Shack
properties.opinion: Jan 9-10, 2021 - When I went there were 3 campsites, campsite 3 having no bear box. There were some frozen pools of water a few hundred feet upstream of the campground. Bear boxes secure. Ground even.

properties.name: Camping municipal La Prairie
properties.opinion:
Showers and toilets are in sufficient number and clean. Very low price 6€ for a night in a tent.
Electricity on all pitches but no wifi. Used one night during a cycling trip. Great experience

properties.name: Café-Restaurant molina
properties.opinion: Essen ist eigentlich ganz lecker, es dauert jedoch ewig bis es kommt. Dann teilweise schon kalt.

properties.name: Villaggio Ialillo
properties.opinion:
Ombra discreta, ma gli alberi producono resina fastidiosa. 
Servizi discreti, comunque puliti.
Presenza di animazione

properties.name: Area Camper Caravan Lido Mirage
properties.opinion: Campeggio molto di base e con poca manutenzione, due stelle solo perché ha una bella ombra

properties.name: Campingplatz Neßhof
properties.opinion:
This camp site is located in a very beautiful environment, close to nature, but also close to the city. The reception wasn't overly friendly (German: "norddeutsche Freundlichkeit"), but since we weren't here to make friends, that's probably okay.

The toilets are clean, our pitch however reeked a bit of, well, "animal poo", but we did not spend too much time on our pitch, so that's something we could live with. For roughly 22 Euros per night for two people, this is an "okay" camp site.

properties.name: Waldesruh-Camping
properties.opinion: Since we only wanted to stay one night and did not need any electricity, we were allowed to use the camper van area at the entrance of the camp site for roughly 15 Euros per night. What a bargain! The showers and restrooms were very, very clean, as were the pitches, and the nice "Stübchen" (a small bistro with fast food and beverages) was a nice extra. In addition, the owners were super-friendly, warm-hearted and very welcoming. Shoutout to Jürgen! We'll visit again if we're ever in the area.

properties.name: Camping De Boskant
properties.opinion: Friendly camp site with nice pitches. The restrooms and showers were clean and the price (20 EUR per night) was more than fair. Maastricht can be visited either by bike (roughly half an hour) or via train.

properties.name: Frauenbad Arbon
properties.opinion: Diese stelle ist sowohl für Schwimmer als auch Padller kaum bis unmöglich nutzbar.Man muss sich mühsam durch knietiefen Schlamm kämpfen bs man im Wasser ist,kommt man raus ist man eingedeckt mit Schlamm.Die Dusche mit der man sich abpsülen könnte existiert zwar,ist aber schon das Ganze Jahr defekt.

properties.name: Zimmer & z'Morgä Schönenboden
properties.opinion:
Priska und Ueli , betreiben mit viel Leidenschaft ihr  Gasthaus !  Das alte Haus hat viel Charm  und ist liebevoll eingerichtet.
wir genossen mit unseren Kindern wunderschöne Sommerferientage im Schönenboden   !
auch den Blumen und Kräutergarten  mit dem Grill bleiben uns in Bester Erinnerung .... herzlichen Dank

properties.name: Boarderhouse
properties.opinion: Sehr kompetent und gut mit Kindern bei einem SUP Kurs, welcher sehr kurzfristig gebucht werden konnte. Preis/Leistung top!

properties.name: Fritløbsområde Scherfigsvej
properties.opinion:
Small dog park with benches and a waste bin. 
It is not fenced in but there is a fence on one side and bushes on the other sides and the park is a bit lower that the surrounding roads.

properties.name: Meiersalp
properties.opinion:
Sehr feines Essen mit gut bemessenen Portionen und sehr preiswert!
Auch der Wein und Kaffee sind günstig.
Ich kann die Meiersalp nur empfehlen. 
Macht weiter so!

properties.name: Camping du Chant des Oiseaux
properties.opinion:
A bit more on the expensive side, this camp site has a very nice panorama with the sea visible. The sunset is breath taking and the pitches have a fair size. The toilets can be a bit of a walk away, but if you know a shortcut, it's alright. They lack toilet paper and soap, so keep in mind to bring that along.

Access to the beach is easy, at least for regular-fit people, since you need to climb a few stairs. The next city is just a 15-minute walk away.

properties.name: playground
properties.opinion: Hele leuke en avontuurlijke speeltuin

properties.name: playground
properties.opinion: Leuke speeltuin voor kleinere kindjes

properties.name: Boerencamping Boerhoes
properties.opinion: Fijne rustige camping met ok toilet- en douchevoorzieningen en hartelijk ontvangst. Ik stond hier 1 nacht met een trekkerstentje terwijl ik het Vechtdalpad wandelde. Vanaf de boerderijcamping wandel je zo de dijk over de uiterwaarde van de Vecht is. Eerst weiland, dan kom je bij een recent gegraven nevengeul waar je heerlijk kunt zwemmen (met stijger en zwemtrap), verderop tussen de nevengeul en de Vecht een mooi langzaam verwilderende bloemenzee (als je op het juiste moment komt).

properties.name: Camping Anna' s Hoeve
properties.opinion: Fijne rustige camping met goede toilet- en douchevoorzieningen en hartelijk ontvangst. Ik stond hier 1 nacht met een trekkerstentje terwijl ik het Vechtdalpad wandelde. Zonsondergang bekijken vanaf de oever van de Vecht is een van de mogelijkheden, net als zwemmen in de Vecht.

properties.name: Søndermarken Hundeskov
properties.opinion:
Nice big dog park with gravel paths between lush lawns and huge trees.

The dog part is not actually fenced off. But is it part of the Søndermarken park, making up about almost half of it. And Søndermarken park is mostly fenced in except for the exits.  In particular there is a fence towards the south end at Valby Langgade. So you have to keep track of where you dog can be off leash (check any of the information boards) but you do not have to worry much about you four legged friend running onto the road.

properties.name: Trekking-Camp Schwarzenbach
properties.opinion:
Von allen Trekkingplätzen im Nordschwarzwald, die ich bisher gesehen habe hat mir dieser wohl am besten gefallen.
Zwar gibt es Im Gegensatz zu den Camps Bösellbach und Seibelseckle keine Hütte aber die Lage ist recht nett. Einen Punkt Abzug gibt es von mir für ein Problem das jedoch fast alle Plätze im Schwarzwald haben. Laute Motorräder die auf der anderen Seite der Talsperre vorbei rasen stören ganz gewaltig.

properties.name: Camping am See
properties.opinion: Great spot!

properties.name: Die Campinginsel
properties.opinion:
Sehr schöner Campingplatz direkt an der Pegnitz. Das Restaurant hat gutes Essen und ein der Stadt angemessenes Bierangebot. Die Sanitäranlagen sind erstklassig. Die Innenstadt erreicht man über einen Linienbus direkt am Eingang. Wer ein Fahrrad hat ist da natürlich flexibler.

Very nice campsite directly located on the banks of the river Pegnitz. The Restaurant features good local food and famous local franconian beers. Sanitary facilities are top notch. Downtown Bamberg can be reached by public bus service. However I would recommend bringing a bicycle.

properties.name: Yuicery
properties.opinion: leckere vegane Bowls

properties.name: Yuicery
properties.opinion: leckere Bowls

properties.name: La Solane
properties.opinion: Loved staying here. Excellent facilities, really nice people and so much space around each camping plot. Also, a lovely river on site with a waterfall and bathing pool. Highly recommended!

properties.name: Kalvebod hundehegn
properties.opinion:
It is big dog park (7 ha) with lots of trees, bushes, grass, flowers, etc.  There is a small muddy pond in the middle
There are no waste bins, so you either have to carry your poop bags back home or not pick up after your dog (this is the posted rules, which some people does read, because there is a pile of full bags on the ground at the entrance)

There is no drinking water. But there a picnic table in each end.
The park is shaped like a triangle with the railroad on one side, the motorway on another side, and the Copenhagen shooting range on the third side. So there is some noise. But not so much that the dogs care about it. And it might be good for some dogs to get used to gunshots.

Parking is at the end of Selinevej which is convenient if you travel on the Øresundsmotorway.

properties.name: Hundewiese Oldenburg Nadorst
properties.opinion:
Not fenced in but far away from any motorized traffic.

properties.name: Natur' O Médoc
properties.opinion:
Very relaxing site with chilled owners! ✌️ Instead of regular pitches, everyone is free to setup camp wherever they want. The place boasts some trees, so it is easy to find some shade. The toilets lack toilet paper, but are otherwise very clean. There are enough sinks for everyone, and it's even possible to use a washing machine. Electricity is also available (for a small fee), as is an outdoor pool (no additional fee). Since its roads and ways are unlit, the site becomes quite dark at night, so depending on how close to the toilets you stay, it's good to have a flashlight around.

Tip: At 6 PM, a small "restaurant" opens right next to the main camping ground, where olives, bread, cold beer and wine is served. That area feels like straight from a relaxing "festival", with makeshift sofas and comfy chairs. We highly recommend you visit here, especially before sunset.

properties.name: Hackerspace Brussels
properties.opinion:
We were looking for a space to organize our Openstreetmap mapathon and HSBXL was very open to letting us use their space. I must say Wouter, who was overseeing the space at the time, was VERY welcoming. Noticed I was wearing a mask (no requirement at the time of writing this) and immediately asked if he should open a window for me (to get some fresh air).

The space itself is (at the time of writing) located in a pretty cool and unique location, an old office building. It definitely fits with the hackerspace feel. At first it seems hard to find but when you enter the courtyard it's located at, you immediately realize you're at the right place. As with most hackerspaces, I assume(?), the fridge/snackstorage works with a trust system where you just deposit the money of whatever you take. (you can pay with cash, bankcard, bank transfer).

It's a shame this location might disappear by the end of the year, but i'm sure they'll find something with a similar vibe!

Dieses Angebot von Thurgau Tourismus kann ich nicht empfehlen.

properties.name: Wohnmobilstellplatz Niederrodenbach
properties.opinion: Der Stellplatz wurde im April 2021 gebaut, Ver- und Entsorgung (die ein bisschen abseits an der Bulauhalle liegt) ist daher topmodern, inklusive Bodeneinlass. Sehr angenehm. 100 Liter Wasser kosten 1 €. Der Stellplatz selbst ist kostenlos, nur wer Strom möchte, muss zahlen (1 € für 2 kWh). Der Boden ist relativ eben, aber geschottert, was immer ein bisschen Schweinerei bedeutet. Das, zusammen mit dem öfter mal auftretenden Gebell von der Hundewiese und dem Geballer vom Schützenhaus nebenan führt zu einem Stern Abzug, aber ansonsten echt ein netter Platz. Die Bäume spenden ein bisschen Schatten, haben aber teilweise auch recht niedrige Äste. Die Straße direkt am Platz ist mäßig befahren, nachts ist hier gar nichts mehr los und der Platz ist sehr ruhig. Oh, und er ist beleuchtet. Der Wald direkt nebenan lädt zum Spazieren oder Geocachen ein. Alles in allem: empfehlenswert.

properties.name: RÅG
properties.opinion: RÅG sets themselves apart from the rest of cafes in Uddevalla, with their alternative vibes in both interior design and food menu. One of the rooms often have Artwork for sale, which is a collaboration between RÅG and local artists. There are some good vegan options but if RÅG wants a 5 star rating from me, they need to expand those options further. Also the coffee could be a little better. properties.name: Pałac Kultury
properties.opinion:
W czasie budowy pałacu oraz z okazji jego otwarcia polska ekipa nakręciła kolorowe filmy (Ślubujemy 1952, Powrót na Stare Miasto 1954, Niedzielny poranek 1955), a zagraniczni fotoreporterzy (np. John H. Schultz ze Stanów Zjednoczonych i Paul Almasy z Francji) wykonali kolorowe fotografie, dzięki czemu znany jest wygląd czystego, nowego Pałacu Kultury i Nauki oraz jego ogromnych, drewnianych i niesczerniałych jeszcze okien.

W 1956 rozpoczęła się seria samobójczych skoków z tarasu widokowego na 30 piętrze, na wysokości 114 metrów – najpierw skoczył Francuz, po nim jeszcze siedmiu Polaków. Po tych incydentach zdecydowano się na założenie krat na tarasie.

properties.name: Burgstelle Hebelstein
properties.opinion: 2020-11-10 Besuch der Anlage. Am Punkt, wie er in OSM ausgewiesen wird, ist kein Hinweis darauf zu finden, dass dort jemals etwas war. Das ganze Gebiet im Umkreis von etwa 100 m wurde abgeschritten und genau geprüft. Keine Mauerreste, keine kleinsten Erhebungen oder Senken konnten gefunden werden. Einziger Hinweis ist die LIDAR-Auswertung als Hillshade (Foto). Dort findet man eine feine Struktur, die daruf hinweisen könnte, dass dort mal was war (feine Kreuze als Markierungen auf dem Hillshadebild.

properties.name: Burgstelle Boppensol
properties.opinion:
Über die Burgstelle sind sehr wenige Informationen verfügbar:
Gemeinde Boppelsen: 
.... Die de Bobpinsolo's sollen eine Burg an der Lägern bewohnt haben, doch fehlen bis anhin jegliche Spuren einer solchen Behausung. ...
Ortsbegehung am 8. November 2020:
Der Ort ist schwer zu finden, da mitten im Waldgebiet. Jedoch mit Hilfe von QField, OSM und einer Hillshade, DTM 2014, Kt. Zürich, 50cm, konnte der Ort identifiziert werden. Dort nur Bäume und Gebüsch. Keine einzige bedeutende Überhöhung konnte identifiziert werden. Es sind auch keine Steine zu finden, die auf ein Gemäuer hinweisen. Auch wurde die Umgebung mit einem Radius von ca. 100m untersucht. Jedoch auch dort keinen kleinsten Hinweis auf ein früheres Gebäude.

properties.name: Burgstelle Boppensol
properties.opinion: It is still not clear where exactly the location was. To have something in the hand I created from the DTM 2014 50cm of the canton Zürich a hillshade of the place. Maybe this will help for further investigation.

properties.name: Brocken
properties.opinion:
Der, mit 1141 Metern, höchste Berg im Harz ist das Ausflugsziel im südwestlichen Niedersachsen. Die Startpunkte für die Wanderungen zum Gipfel sind aus allen Richtungen mit dem öffentlichen Personennahverkehr als auch mit dem Individualverkehr sehr gut zu erreichen.

Wanderwege
Das Wegenetz des Harzes hat für alle Erfahrungsstufen etwas zu bieten. Ob es sich um einen absoluten Anfänger handelt, der nur zum Brocken möchte und auf dem Rückweg die Brockenbahn verwendet oder der erfahrene Fernwanderer, der sich auf einer der vielen Fernwanderrouten, die den Harz kreuzen, befindet.

Klimatische Besonderheiten
Der Harz hat auf Grund seiner Lage auf klimatisch einiges zu bieten. Während es in den Tälern rund um den Brocken angenehmes Wetter haben kann sieht es auf dem Brocken oftmals ganz anders aus. Ohne wetterfeste Kleidung und entsprechendes Schuhwerk würde ich den Aufstieg nicht wagen. 

Fazit
Wanderwege für alle Erfahrungsstufen und gute Erreichbarkeit

properties.name: Brisen

Auf dem Weg zurück ins Tal über die andere Seite haben wir einen spektakulären Platz für unser Zelt gefunden. Eine windige Nacht, aber die Aussicht auf Sonnenuntergang und den Sonnenaufgang am Morgen haben für alles entlohnt.

properties.name: Fronalpstock

Ein sehr angenehmes Erlebnis, und die Aussicht oben absolut atemberaubend! Eine Woche später sind wir noch einmal zurück gekommen, der Schnee war größtenteils weg und wir konnten mühelos wandern und die Aussicht geniessen. Nun sind wir von Stoos zu Klingenstock hoch gewandert und dann den Grat entlang bis Fronalpstock. Ein wunderbares Erlebnis!

Die Preise sind auf ungarischem Niveau. Manchmal gibt es auch traditionelle ungarische Hausmusik. Wenn man am Ende eines Abends viel Würfelglück hat, muss man sogar gar nichts bezahlen...

properties.opinion: Lovely Tibetan restaurant with great traditional food. Run by a family, they really make an effort to make you a good evening. Nice for a date or casually eating. Love the momos and their udon noodles

properties.name: Kahwa el Salam
properties.opinion: We went here for breakfast and it turned out to be a real hidden gem in terms of coziness and beautiful interior. Food was ok, we had an omelette with pickled veggies, topped with grated cheese. The regular omelette without the pickles is probably better. Service was very nice and the atmosphere was relaxed and cheerful.

properties.name: Gellért Hill
properties.opinion: It is a very nice walk up Gellert Hill, through a large park with windy paths and sculptures along the way. On top, you have a fantastic view over Budapest. A variety of stalls offering drinks and snacks makes it a great afternoon or early evening tour, especially on a warm and sunny day.

properties.name: Napfényes étterem
properties.opinion: Nice vegan restaurant serving vegan versions of traditional Hungarian meals and more. Great for anyone who wants to explore the local cuisine without meat. Interior was well-maintained but looked a bit old-fashioned. But the food and great service made up for it.

properties.name: Tihany
properties.opinion: Cozy historical village on the Tihany peninsula on the northern shore of Lake Balaton. Very well maintained and a real tourist magnet for the whole of Hungary. The village's website offers a downloadable pocket guide, a video and even a virtual tour. Besides the beautiful landscape one can enjoy the relics of the folk architecture such as the peasant houses. Had a great traditional meal at the Gulyas Udvar Etterem. Might become very crowded during high season (in March it was perfect though).

properties.name: Gulyás Udvar Étterem
properties.opinion: Had lunch here during our visit of Tihany, a picturesque historical village on a peninsula of Lake Balaton. This restaurant might look very touristic from outside, but inside you find a truly traditional cozy place that serves simple and very well-made local food, such as the cod paprikas I had. The waiter was very engaged and pleasant, and helped us to find the right meal according to our tastes. It was a great experience.

properties.name: Gettó Gulyás
properties.opinion: Great restaurant serving traditional gulyas and paprikas. Elegant and cozy industrial-style interior. Had two vegetarian dishes: one with giant white beans, topped with a fried egg and fresh peppers and onions that was fantastic. Second dish was good, but the mushrooms were a bit watery, so it was not as great as the bean dish. Great white wine recommendation (Tokaji) that fit perfectly.

properties.name: Budapest Baristas
properties.opinion: Went here for breakfast and loved the food! Creative vegetarian/vegan options. Had dishes with oven-roasted pumpkin and another one with sweet potato, topped with different veggies or eggs/salmon. The coffee was great, too. Interior is cozy and interesting with the gallery, but overall quite small. At some point there was a queue of people ordering directly at the counter, which filled up the whole room.

properties.name: Great Market Hall
properties.opinion: Large historic indoor market in Budapest, built in 1897 and renovated in 1997. The architecture alone is already worth a visit. Very nice to wander around the many food stalls with local produce or popular Hungarian food items, eateries, souvenir shops.

properties.name: Kettinger
properties.opinion: Recht teuer. Laugengebäck ist ordentlich.

properties.name: Refugio Emilio Frey
properties.opinion: Cool shelter located 1700mts high on the top of Cerro Catedral with an amazing 12km hike passing through forests, hills, and cliffs with the flowers and clear water. It has it all for the beginner hikers. Great in Spring/Summer seasons, when you can see the forest in between at its best. Make sure to take water and a walking stick along with some snacks for the way. The last hour can be tricky, as it is super steep. Wanna sleep/camp there? book in advance: http://refugiofreybariloche.com/

properties.name: Colonia del Sacramento
properties.opinion: If you are in Buenos Aires and want to get away from all the noise, this small town is the perfect place for a day of relax and history. Disputed between the Spanish and Portuguese Crowns until almost the end of the XVIII century, it is the perfect plan for a day (by boat from Bs As or car/bus from Montevideo), where you can see the colonial architecture and enjoy the food and the sun. Make sure to check the Raddisson Hotel's pool if it is too warm! :D

properties.name: Bohemios
properties.opinion:
Almost all soccer clubs in Buenos Aires have restaurants: this is the typical Neighbourhood club restaurant in the city, where you will be able to grasp the neighbourhood culture and how much people care about their sports club - especially if they play soccer there! great food! good quality and very friendly staff! 

Not so good if you don't eat meat: they do not have so many options for vegetarians.

properties.name: La Fonda del Tío
properties.opinion:
Great place to try good plates that combines the best of Argentinian and Italian food tradition - good environment and really cheap. Try the "milanesa" if you eat meat and the "canelones" if you are a vegetarian. After 9pm you will need to queue, so make sure to either book in advance or go beforehand - and be careful: the sizes are really big! you can definitely share a portion.

Great for groups, families and friends, if you are looking for something romantic this is not the place to go.

properties.name: Cerro Campanario
properties.opinion:
Definitely one of the best views in Bariloche, you can reach the top of cerro Campanario either by foot (easy level hike) or cablecar - the ticket is around 3 EUR. Definetely worth it if you want to check the lakes around Bariloche and get an idea of the extension of The Andes. 

The Cerro is right at the start of "Circuito Chico": a 24km road through mountains full of hiking trails. So a good idea is always to wake up early, get to the top fo the mountain, and at around 11am start the Circuito.

properties.name: Wroclaw
properties.opinion: Beautiful city, a lot of culture to explore. And fantastic selection of restaurants, from traditional Polish food to exotic options such as Peruvian.

properties.name: Château de Chillon
properties.opinion: Visited the castle in winter, so it was a bit cold. Can only imagine how amazing it must be on a sunny day, with the lake around and the walls warmed by the sun. It was a fantastic experience to wander through its many rooms, and discover historical artifacts from its history spanning a whole millennium. Was touched by the story of François Bonivard who was imprisoned there and inspired a poem of Lord Byron: The Prisoner of Chillon.

properties.name: Peruwiana
properties.opinion: Great Peruvian fusion food, fantastic drinks, and nice atmosphere! Interior is decorated with a lot of wood, dark green colours, and plants. The red drink on the picture was a delicious, interesting non-alcoholic hot drink with fresh raspberry and rosemary.

properties.name: Reformierte Kirche
properties.opinion: Visited a wonderful organ concert in this church on Sunday 2nd Feb. The concert took place on the organ-gallery, a loft that can be reached over stairs. I was impressed with the acoustics and the quality of the performance. Learned later that the church has been designated to cultural and spiritual events, and as a place for community gatherings, under the name CityKircheZug. Will definitely visit other cultural events here in the future.

properties.name: Maag MusicHall
properties.opinion: Visited the Van Gogh Alive exhibition at Maag yesterday. Great experience in terms of sound and light quality. From the outside and also inside the building could benefit from modernisation to make it more welcoming.

properties.name: Lucerne
properties.opinion: Very nice town to visit: beautiful old town, nice modern art museum, views on Rigi, Pilatus and the lake.

properties.name: Seattle
properties.opinion:
Beautiful and diverse.
Too corporate.
Uber cliquey.
Feels like a mono-culture sometimes merely because so many people do not talk to eachother or help out one another.
Growing and changing a lot.
I feel like a little more openness to establishing connections with different people is all this area actually needs.

properties.name: Klaips
properties.opinion: Nice setting and staff. Reasonable prices.

properties.name: Landbierparadies
properties.opinion: Ordentliches Essen mit gutem Bier. Die Portionen könnten manchmal etwas größer sein.

properties.name: Hong-Kong Food Paradise
properties.opinion: That restaurant has just been recommended by a friend.

properties.name: Juan Long
properties.opinion: A Chinese restaurant in the heart of Zug, Suan Long is a good place for a meal and a beer with friends. Food is good but not amazing, and there are no original vegetarian dishes, but rather the type of options where meat was replaced with tofu. Staff is friendly but often looks tired. It can be quite smoky inside due to the open kitchen where a lot of frying is going on.

properties.name: SaarowTherme
properties.opinion:
Great view from the spa area and chill out room, 1st floor, small building.

Very nice located at the lake.

They could improve with more healthy food on the menu.

properties.name: Restaurant De Jong
properties.opinion: Very interesting food, great service.

properties.name: Baumgarten
properties.opinion: Speciality is Pizzas with thick bottom.

properties.name: Bürgenstock
properties.opinion: Bürgenstock is great for a day trip from Zurich, Luzern or Zug. Nice trails on top for walks, and amazing view over alps and Lake Lucerne. Also, quite a few fine dining restaurants around, as well as a spa.

properties.name: Zugerberg
properties.opinion: Nice destination for a hike up from the town of Zug. Hike takes around 2 hours and gives a beautiful view on the Zuger lake. On top there is a restaurant with simple local food to enjoy before hiking back down again. Good views on the alps, on some days you can even see Eiger, Jungfrau and Mönch.

properties.name: Brasserie Nestor
properties.opinion: We had the two vegetarian options on the menu and they were both very interesting and refined dishes. A bit too much grains for us, especially in the mushroom porridge, but nevertheless balanced and interesting tastes. Atmosphere also nice with large glass windows and a minimalist retro decor.

properties.name: Gotthärdli
properties.opinion: I regularly eat at this fantastic Thai restaurant. They have a bar downstairs which the restaurant shouldn't be confused with. The food is pretty authentic and there are sufficient vegetarian options. The restaurant is located in a historic and well kept house that displays original wood covered walls, with windows towards the lake. A pleasure for the eye as well.

properties.name: Gütsch
properties.opinion:
We hiked up to Gütsch on a winter afternoon when it was already getting dark. Had a beautiful view over Lucerne from there. The restaurant also looks very nice, but didn't have the time to visit it. 
Next time we will definitely visit the little sculpture park there as it seemed interesting (closes at 18:00). For the way down we took the little funicular. Definitely recommend for a day trip to Luzern.
